def _get_grouper(
    obj,
    key=None,
    axis=0,
    level=None,
    sort=True,
    observed=False,
    mutated=False,
    validate=True,
):
    group_axis = obj._get_axis(axis)

    if axis == 0:  # Grouping by index
        # Logic for grouping by index
        pass
    elif axis == 1:  # Grouping by columns
        if key in obj.columns:
            gpr = obj[key]
            ping = Grouping(
                group_axis,
                gpr,
                obj=obj,
                name=key,
                level=level,
                sort=sort,
                observed=observed,
                in_axis=True,
            )
            grouper = BaseGrouper(group_axis, [ping], sort=sort, mutated=mutated)
            return grouper, [], obj
        else:
            raise KeyError(key)
    else:
        raise ValueError("Invalid axis value")
